title: Google\Cloud\GkeMultiCloud\V1\AzureNodeConfig
name: AzureNodeConfig
description:
Parameters that describe the configuration of all node machines on a given node pool.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AzureNodeConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.vm_size
params.description: Optional. The Azure VM size name. Example: Standard_DS2_v2. See Supported VM sizes for options. When unspecified, it defaults to Standard_DS2_v2.

params.name: data.root_volume
params.description: Optional. Configuration related to the root volume provisioned for each node pool machine. When unspecified, it defaults to a 32-GiB Azure Disk.

params.name: data.tags
params.description: Optional. A set of tags to apply to all underlying Azure resources for this node pool. This currently only includes Virtual Machine Scale Sets. Specify at most 50 pairs containing alphanumerics, spaces, and symbols (.+-=_:@/). Keys can be up to 127 Unicode characters. Values can be up to 255 Unicode characters.

params.name: data.image_type
params.description: Optional. The OS image type to use on node pool instances. Can have a value of ubuntu, or windows if the cluster enables the Windows node pool preview feature. When unspecified, it defaults to ubuntu.

params.name: data.ssh_config
params.description: Required. SSH configuration for how to access the node pool machines.

params.name: data.proxy_config
params.description: Optional. Proxy configuration for outbound HTTP(S) traffic.

params.name: data.config_encryption
params.description: Optional. Configuration related to vm config encryption.

params.name: data.taints
params.description: Optional. The initial taints assigned to nodes of this node pool.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Optional. The initial labels assigned to nodes of this node pool. An object containing a list of "key": value pairs. Example: { "name": "wrench", "mass": "1.3kg", "count": "3" }.
